## Grammar

- Past tense forms of פָּעַל verbs with different subjects (3rd person masculine/feminine singular)
- Imperative forms (בֹּא, come)
- Basic noun-adjective agreement (masculine/feminine)
- Definite article ה- with nouns
- Prepositions: בַּ- (in/at), מִן (from), אֶל (to/towards), יַד (beside)
- Negation with לֹא
- Basic sentence structure with verbs and subjects
- Conjunction וְ (and) connecting clauses
- Direct object marker (implicit in verb forms)
- Adverbial expressions (מְאֹד, שׁוּב, יוֹתֵר)
